sub_title: FullStack software developer at  Edge Impulse
summary: Born in Uruguay, lately living in The Netherlands, I finished my degree in Telecommunications Engineering with a strong focus in Electronics. By then, I wrote my thesis about applied image processing for the medical industry and built a low cost prototype for Videonystagmography based on C++ code and a low cost webcam. After graduation, I studied Computer Sciences and taught electronics and signal processing at the Department of Electrical Engineering of the Catholic University. During that time I participated in several research projects, mostly linked to signal processing for both image and audio. I worked for some years as an independent consultant building electrical systems and programming PLC devices for industry automation. I learned software development basics during highschool and I kept improving my knowledge by working in several projects of all sizes. I also studied and worked in Sound Engineering and Acoustic Modelling for a small company in Montevideo and later as an independent consultant. For the last 10 years I mostly worked in software projects, focusing now in distributed and scalable event-driven applications.
